input.prompt:
Search for duplicate class definitions in the codebase. 

1. Find all class definitions using pattern "^class \w+" across all Python files
2. Extract class names and their file locations
3. Identify any class names that appear in multiple files (duplicates)
4. Report which classes are duplicated and in which files they appear

Focus on the cortical/ directory and any referenced/imported modules. Be thorough - check both the main source and test directories.

Return a structured report showing:
- Total number of class definitions found
- Any duplicate class names with their file locations
- Whether these duplicates are intentional (e.g., test mocks) or potentially problematic
